    "kernel": "4.15.0-36-generic",
    "notes": "The Game itself is playable. With exception of the two issues noted below I do not see a difference to the windows version.\n\nIssues are freezes in gameplay for accessing certain menues (like 15 second wait time until you get to the hacking screen). The game never crashes though, even audiobooks continue to play in the background. Its not a disadvantage in gameplay, but its very very annoying. You have to open a lot of these bugged menues during gameplay, so this is the point, that brings the game down to bronze from me.\n\nSecond issue are that the high-res versions of some textures (like certain posters or NPC-bodies) fail to load, even if you are standing close to them (and yeah, the age of the game and graphic engine is accounted for - I know the game from windows). So far, there was one (non-critical) section, where this was a real issue: I needed to read a door-code on a piece of paper, that was just a mash of pixels. Impossible without help from the internet.\nOtherwise it just makes the game uglier - a shame, since it diminishes the excellent atmosphere of the game.\n\n(tested from beginning until farmers market level)",
